cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the recognition of handwritten characters using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of advanced neural network architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of datasets and performance evaluation, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
